The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Krishnagar, May 9: A rich scrap metal dealer of Plassey allegedly kidnapped his sons private tutor and demanded Rs 3 lakh as compensation for the 12-year-old boys indiscipline.

 The Class V student failed in school this year and was caught stealing money from his fathers purse regularly. Subir Chowdhury, the English teacher of Borochandghar High School at Kaligunj, 150 km from Calcutta, lodged a police complaint last night, saying he was released on Monday after promising the father Rs 70,000. Manab Modak has also lodged a complaint, accusing his sons teacher of leading him astray.

 Calcutta: The city and its neighbouring areas experienced intermittent power cuts on Wednesday night as the State Electricity Distri-bution Company scaled down its supply to CESC from 400 mw to 150 mw. 

 Barasat: Bangaldeshis Ajay Thakur and Srinath Rai have been arrested from North 24-Parganas Swarupnagar. They were charged with having terrorist links.

 Burdwan: Uttam Ghosh strangled his wife Shyamali, 30, to death. Police said he had lost his sanity after his potato crop was destroyed.




